		"description": "<p id=\"docs-internal-guid-39cb81cd-7fff-d098-3126-f48aad287e0c\" dir=\"ltr\">The black handle of this ritual dagger is carved with intricate images of the hearth: healing herbs and flowers, as well as berries and wheat. The handle has three bands of carnelian at set intervals.</p><p dir=\"ltr\">Each of the three bands represents a charge. As an action, you may choose to expend a charge to cast the @UUID[Compendium.a5e.a5e-spells.Item.c9itysok7lr2ai51]{Scorching Ray} spell. If you choose to expend more than one charge at a time, treat it as if the spell was cast at a higher level (maximum two levels higher than 2nd). Charges that are used do not replenish, and a carnelian band disappears for each one expended. Once all three charges have been used, the athame reverts to a mundane weapon with the statistics of a dagger.</p>",
